        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 3000, 3900 FC, 4000 models and all models with Vari-Rate rear suspension.
                </para>
                <para>The four inch wide springs for the 3000 and 4000 Model chassis now include a 10,000 pound taper
                    leaf unit that comes with sealed bushings and modified pins. Multileaf units, at this time, retain
                    the current non-sealed bushings.
                </para>
                <para>Service parts, as supplies are exhausted, will begin supplying internally sealed bushings and pins
                    with revised grease grooves in place of the old parts. These components are interchangeable and
                    sealed bushings will extend service life (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9703011">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <para>The three inch wide spring used on the 3900 FC front engine chassis, and all chassis with
                    Vari-Rate rear suspensions, has new style bushings available for improved service life.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9703011" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9703011.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. New Spring Bushing</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The new spring bushing comes with the seals in place. The seals cannot be serviced
                            separately.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
