        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <stitle>TSI 97-03-01RB - Steer Axle and Vari-Rate Spring Bushings and Pins - Wear Limits</stitle>
            <title>WEAR LIMITS</title>
            <para>All suspensions using smooth bore pins should be scheduled for bushing and/or pin replacement when the
                difference between the pin O.D. and bushing I.D. exceeds .085 inch clearance. If the clearance is .120
                inch or more, replace immediately.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>New bushing and pin assemblies are designed to have up to .012 inch clearance to provide
                        optimum performance.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>A simple spring bushing installation tool can be made by plug welding a 2 X 2 X 3/8 inch plate with a
                1 inch diameter hole onto a used spring pin as illustrated in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9703012">Figure 2</hotlnk>. Driver should be clean and lightly greased when installing
                a bushing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9703012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9703012.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Bushing Installation Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The spring eye bushing is installed so that the bushing seam (split) is at the top (12
                        o'clock) position in the spring eye bore +/- 15 degrees. The bushing in the spring bracket is
                        installed with the bushing seam (split) at the bottom (6 o'clock) position. No adhesive is used
                        for bushing retention.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
